      • getSubjectToken

        public java.lang.String getSubjectToken()
        A security token that represents the identity of the party on behalf of whom exchange is being made. Typically, the subject of this token will be the subject of the security token issued. Token is base64-encoded.

        The property is required when the value of the getGrantType() property is urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:token-exchange.

        This property is currently required. In the future, the class may support grant-types other than urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:token-exchange for which the value may be null.
        Returns:
        The current value of the property.
